Both required output files are now in the working directory:

- `transcript.json` (34 KB, 20 iterations, 54 hypotheses, 54 analyses, schema-validated)
- `analysis_summary.txt` (10 KB)

**Headline finding:** `feature_008` is a randomized treatment indicator (40.2% prevalence, balanced across every other feature). Its overall effect on `objective_response` (OR ~3 in the full cohort) is entirely concentrated in the subgroup defined by

> `feature_013 = 0` AND `feature_015 = 0` AND `feature_021 = 0` AND `feature_027 = 0`

Within that subgroup (n=15,681; 31.4%), treatment lifts ORR from **17.2% → 79.8%** (RD +62.6 pp [95% CI 61.4–63.8], OR 19.0 [17.6–20.6], NNT 1.6). Outside it, treatment is essentially inert (RD +0.8 pp). The four modifiers act in a **saturation pattern**: any single one ON kills the effect; pairs/triples don't suppress further. They are predictive, not prognostic — within untreated patients all four have small or null effects on baseline ORR. Independent prognostic-only factors are `feature_001`, `log(feature_022)`, `log(feature_020)`, `log(feature_024)`, and `feature_002`.
